<br>
Big Fellowship IV by George Wilson    </FONT></TD></TR><TR><TD WIDTH="10%" VALIGN="TOP"><font face="Haettenschweiler, Tahoma, Arial, sans-serif" size="5" COLOR="#000000">Strategy</Font></TD><TD><font face="Arial, sans-serif" size="2">This deck is mainly to be used at a tournement where people play twilight Nazgul. Against other decks, this deck is not packed against, but may still hold up. The reason why this is a Fun deck, is because of the adventure value. Getting the fellowship out is important. The sites all work well. I suggest bidding no more than 4. If you win and you&#39;re facing a Nazgul deck, go second. Weathertop is crucial for a good Nazgul deck. If they get Aragorn or Sam, than you can too. Bag End is your advantage. Nobody that I know plays the Gaffer, therefore, you get an advantage over your opponent. <br>
<br>
My Styles:<br>
 Merry, Friend to Sam. A lot of people play him, but not many realize his great value. Along with Farmer &quot;the healing&quot; maggot, he can give people strength bonuses whenever he&#39;s ready. Few people can stop him.<br>
 Bag End. A not very popular site as sites go, but a great one. Using the Gaffer is great! He can heal Frodo, or Sam. Hobbit Party guests, AND Frodo can heal The Gaffer and Farmer Maggot.<br>
 The Gaffer. Not used often. Has great use. See Bag End.<br>
 Hobbit Party Guest. Heals Farmer Maggot, himself, The Gaffer, AND is non-unique. Hmmm... we can have a healing system.<br>
 Albert Dreary. Known to few people, this man, played by Peter Jackson, can eliminate Swarms, Armory, Worry, and any other Moria or Isengard condition. If you ask me, a good choice for a deck.<br>
 Staff Asunder. Another good card. Destroys our good friend The Bally, Witch-king, Enquea, or any minion, if he can take two wounds and discard a staff.<br>
 The Splendor of Their Banners. Good for archery. At site 9, it can giv you +2 archery (if legolas is fully healed). That extra vitality wasted. Good against swarms.<br>
 Uruk Captain. This minion can save you at site 9. He can bring on another minion. If you play multiple captains, you can really surprise your opponent.<br>
 Uruk Soldier. Discard the top card of your opponent&#39;s draw deck. Could be their only bally, Lurtz, or Witch-King.<br>
 Orthanc Assassin. Archer with 10 strength. Need I say more?<br>
 Orthanc Berserker. He exhausts your opponent&#39;s companions.<br>
 One of you must do this. Good card against Large fellowships. Look it up yourself.<br>
<br>
N E Wayz, Gotta Go.<br>
<br>
               -George </FONT></TD></TR><TR><TD WIDTH="10%" VALIGN="TOP"><font face="Haettenschweiler, Tahoma, Arial, sans-serif" size="5" COLOR="#000000"> </Font></TD><TD><font face="Arial, sans-serif" size="2">DeckTech <BR> For the Players, By the Players  <BR>www.decktech.net </FONT></TD></TR></table> 
